{
  "body": "The term UBERON:0002346 \"neurectoderm\" also has a synonym \"neuroectoderm.\" However, neuroectoderm seems more common amongst the linked cross references, and I also see more results when exact searching Pubmed for neuroectoderm. Are there any reasons why neurectoderm is preferred by UBERON over neuroectoderm?\n\n\n\n",
  "comments": [
    {
      "id": "IC_kwDOAAidd871r0pP",
      "author": {
        "login": "cmungall"
      },
      "authorAssociation": "MEMBER",
      "body": "@dragon-ai-agent please swap label and exact synonym, reference this issue\n\nalso please open an issue on the cell-ontology repo to make a corresponding change to any cl terms (you should find them yourself first to save the cl editors the work)",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-24T22:44:47Z",
      "includesCreatedEdit": false,
      "isMinimized": false,
      "minimizedReason": "",
      "reactionGroups": [],
      "url": "https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3682#issuecomment-4121905743",
      "viewerDidAuthor": false
    }
  ],
  "title": "UBERON:0002346 \"neurectoderm\" vs \"neuroectoderm\"",
  "url": "https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3682"
}

